All new code should be written in Swift. Adhere to Swift 6.0 language features and syntax. Refer to https://docs.swift.org/swift-book/documentation/the-swift-programming-language/revisionhistory/ for latest changes if your code couldn't build and found error that could be caused by the latest changes.

Never use float to hold longitude and latitude. Always use CLLocationDegrees as the type for longitude and latitude.